KB003 — How to Fix Printing Issues
Purpose:  
Provide a repeatable workflow for resolving common printer issues such as offline printers, stuck jobs, spooler failures, and driver problems.

🧭 Steps
Check Print Spooler Service  
Restart if stopped or stuck.

Clear Print Queue  
Delete files in:
C:\Windows\System32\spool\PRINTERS

Verify Printer IP  
Ping the printer’s IP address.

Check Printer Port  
Ensure TCP/IP port matches printer IP.

Check Printer Driver  
Incorrect drivers cause offline status.

Reinstall Printer  
Use the correct driver package.

🧰 Recommended Tool
Use the Network Diagnostic Tool to confirm connectivity:
Network Diagnostics
